# What I Implemented

## 1. Terraform Variables

I created variables to make the infrastructure configurable and reusable.

### Variables Used

* `vol_siz` → Root EBS volume size
* `vol_typ` → Root EBS volume type
* `insta_deta` → EC2 instance type
* `additional_tags` → Extra custom tags

### Benefit

Using variables makes the code flexible and avoids hardcoding values.

---

# 2. Terraform Locals

I created reusable local values for:

* Project name
* Project owner
* Cost center
* Managed by

```hcl
locals {

  project       = "own learning terraform project"
  project_owner = "DevOps guy"
  cost_center   = 30
  managed_by    = "awk"

}
```

### Why Locals?

Locals help reduce repetition and improve maintainability.

Instead of writing the same values multiple times, I can reuse them throughout the Terraform configuration.

---

# 3. Centralized Tagging Strategy

I created a local object called `project_details`.

```hcl
locals {

  project_details = {

    project       = local.project
    project_owner = local.project_owner
    cost_center   = local.cost_center
    managed_by    = local.managed_by

  }

}
```

data "aws_ami" "own_ami_ubuntu_IND" {
  most_recent = true
  owners      = ["099720109477"] # Canonical's AWS account ID

  filter {
    name   = "name"
    values = ["ubuntu/images/hvm-ssd/ubuntu-jammy-22.04-amd64-server-*"]
  }

  filter {
    name   = "virtualization-type"
    values = ["hvm"]
  }
}
[

### Purpose

This local object acts as a centralized common tags map that can be reused across AWS resources.

### Advantage

* Consistent tagging
* Easier management
* Cleaner Terraform code

---

# 4. EC2 Instance Refactoring

I refactored the EC2 instance tags section using Terraform `merge()` function.

```hcl
tags = merge(local.project_details, var.additional_tags)
```

### What `merge()` Does

The `merge()` function combines:

* Common project tags
* Additional custom tags

### Final Tags Applied

```hcl
project       = "own learning terraform project"
project_owner = "DevOps guy"
cost_center   = 30
managed_by    = "awk"
app           = "state_Highway"
```

### Benefit

This approach provides:

* Standardized tagging
* Flexibility for extra tags
* Better resource organization

